  "commentary": "With SPX at 6823 sitting 23 points below the GEX flip at 6846, dealers are currently long gamma and likely buying this dip while providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6900 (+5.8B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the negative gamma pocket at 6700 offers a floor where dealer buying should kick in. Key levels to watch are the 6846 flip strike above (regime change) and the 6850/6875 gamma walls that should act as near-term resistance.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to grind higher toward 6850-6900 but face heavy selling pressure at those levels.",
